==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scunner
<hw>Scun"ner</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Shun</er>.]</ety> <def>To cause to loathe, or feel disgust at.</def>
<mark>[Scot. & Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scunner</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Scunner
<hw>Scun"ner</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To have a feeling of loathing
or disgust; hence, to have dislike, prejudice, or reluctance.</def>
<mark>[Scot. & Prov. Eng.]</mark> <rj><au>C. Kingsley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scunner</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Scunner
<hw>Scun"ner</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A feeling of disgust or loathing;
a strong prejudice; abhorrence; <as>as, to take a <ex>scunner</ex>
against some one</as>.</def> <mark>[Scot. & Prov. Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Carlyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scup</ent>⟦br⟧
